post_text:
Have you heard? Thanks to the USDA, FREE breakfast and lunch are now available for all Midland County children aged 18 and younger through the end of the fall semester! On days your child is at school, they will get lunch on campus; and on at-home learning days they can pick up meals from 10:30am-12:30pm at one of seven locations. MISD Online Academy students can pick up the free meals as well. Visit www.midlandisd.net/fallmeals for a list of locations!

Please note - meals are available on school calendar days only, so on teacher work days like next Monday, Sept. 14 meals will not be availalbe.

Parents: There's still time to enroll for the Midland ISD Online Academy!

The Online Academy is separate from the At-Home Instruction that every student will participate in for the first four weeks of school.

The Online Academy is a long-term virtual commitment. Students can only enter or exit the Online Academy at the end of every grading period.

Applications will be accepted through August 14.

post_text: MISD is pleased to announce that we will hold in-person ceremonies for graduating seniors. These ceremonies will take place on Saturday, May 30. Graduates and their families will be assigned a specific time at one of six locations around the city. This will enable each graduate to walk across the stage, receive a diploma, and be photographed with their family in attendance, all while maintaining social distancing. These events are *in addition* to previously announced plans for virtual graduations at the Big Sky Drive-In. For more information, visit midlandisd.net/seniors2020.

Midland ISD has launched a counseling support hotline to provide further support for our students, families, staff and community members in the wake of the COVID-19 outbreak. The counseling support hotline will provide access to Midland ISD counseling staff 7 a.m.-7p.m. weekdays at 432-240-1439.

The hotline also will provide options to connect with PermiaCare counselors, who are experienced in crisis counseling, at 844-420-3962. PermiaCare is staffed 24 hours a day, seven days a week and is available to any student, staff member or member of the community.

#covid19 #midlandisd #midlandtx #midlandtexas #midland #texas #westtexas

post_text: Based upon currently available information about COVID-19, Midland ISD will remain closed through at least May 1. The safety and well-being of our staff and students is at the forefront of our decision-making as we monitor the fluid nature of this disease. It is our hope that confirming the closure ahead of time will help you make necessary arrangements in caring for your family. We will continue our food service during this time. Stay tuned for more information on our ongoing academic enrichment programs. For updates, please check midlandisd.net/covid19.

post_text:
Beginning Monday, academic enrichment activities for all grade levels will be available at midlandisd.net/enrichment. If you don‚Äôt have internet access, hard copies can be picked up from meal distribution sites from 7:30-8:30 each morning, and during the lunch hour from 11:30-12:30. Activities are built by grade ranges: PK, K-2, 3-5, 6-8, and 9-12. If you have children within each grade range, only one packet will be needed for your family. For example, if you have a kindergarten and second-grade student, you would only need one K-2 packet. All PK-5 packets are available in English and Spanish.

More information is available at www.midlandisd.net/covid19.

Because of the continued spread of COVID-19 and its impact on our community, Midland ISD has made the decision to close all district offices effective Monday, March 23, in an effort to increase social distancing and minimize the chance for community spread. Staff have been directed to work from home while completing their specific job duties as assigned by their supervisor.

This change does not alter the district's commitments regarding the provisions of child nutrition and academic resources.

More information is available at midlandisd.net/covid19.

Thank you to Sibley Nature Center for leading an awesome and engaging biology lesson at Young Women's Leadership Academy of Midland! Students learned about the wildlife of the Llano Estacado by investigating and categorizing the characteristics of mystery skulls and then used field guides to identify which native Texas animal they had.

Sibley will also be be at Santa Rita, De Zavala, Parker, Pease, Franks and Fasken soon to teach our students about local wildlife!

‚ùå Some in the community are saying that Midland ISD isn‚Äôt taking action to address water concerns at Fannin Elementary.

‚úÖ FACT: Both Midland ISD and the city of Midland are having water samples tested and should receive results by the end of this week.

‚ùå There have been rumors that Fannin students don‚Äôt have any water to drink.

‚úÖ FACT: Midland ISD is supplying students and staff with bottled water and will continue to do so until it is determined that a problem does not exist.

‚ùå Midland ISD hasn‚Äôt consulted anyone with expertise in the field of water safety.

‚úÖ FACT: Midland ISD is working closely with the city of Midland, an independent third party environmental expert and independent water labs.
